<br>
I met Arathyn when I was still much of a girl. He had just been brought to Freeport, and was still recovering from being beaten and left for dead by a group of ghouls.<br>
<br>
My father liked Ary, as he was once a paladin as well. He hoped that someday Arathyn would be taking his place at the head of our estate, but my tomboy tendancies shot that hope down quickly.<br>
<br>
I learned how to fight with a sword from Ary. He kept gettings worked by the other squires, and taught me thinking that I would be an easy fight. After a few times of sparing, I proved to be just as good as his classmates, though I couldn't take as many hits.<br>
<br>
Whenever Ary was in that stuff hall, I was reading stories of Norrath and learning to play musical instruments. I had my mother's voice, or at least that's what my father always tells me. Eventually, I joined up with the Bards of Antonica.<br>
<br>
Now that my skills are greatly improved, and a bit above average, Arathyn and I travel all over Eastern Antonica and the isle Faydwer. Even though it gets annoyin, I find his zealousness for justice quite enduring. It sparks a fire in everyone who fights with us, and seems to make them fight harder.<br>
<br>
Well, I'm sure that's more than enough about me.  I'm a BARD, I'll probably have another story ready soon.<br>
<br>
<br>
((OOC NOTE: I am writing a huge, long, background story for Xelena - which will also encompass a lot of Arathyn's life since we're togther and everything. That will go under Hero Heart when it's done. This was just a 2 minute job I posted to Circle of Sisters to introduce myself))<br>
